text: Biryukovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Biryukovsky Selsoviet, Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 1,857 as of 2010. There are 16 streets. == Geography == It is located 7 km ESE from Nachalovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Privolzhsky District, Astrakhan Oblast
title: Biryukovka
